BrainHR Java Services

BrainHR Java Services provides businesses with access to the latest Java technologies and tools to optimize their business operations. Our team of experts has the knowledge and experience to provide businesses with customized solutions that meet their unique needs and requirements. We use various Java software and tools to deliver high-quality services to our clients. These include Java Development Kit (JDK) which is a software development environment used to develop Java applications, Apache Maven which is a build automation tool used for Java projects, and Spring Framework which is a popular Java framework used for building web applications. BrainHR's Java Full Stack Technology services provide a one-stop solution for clients looking to develop, deploy, and maintain Java-based software applications. With a focus on scalability, security, and user-friendliness, BrainHR delivers high-quality software applications that meet the needs of its clients.

BrainHR provides comprehensive Java Full Stack Technology services to clients and customers for product development. These services integrate and combine various tools, coding languages, and platforms to execute a software project using Java & J2EE technologies and frameworks such as JSP, JSTL, Servlets, JDBC, EJB, Java Beans, and Java Security are used for developing Java-based applications, which includes JSP, JSTL, Servlets (3.1, 3.0), JDBC, EJB, Java Beans XSD, JAX-RS, JAX-WS, SOAP, WSDL, Axis, Apache CXF, and Java Security. These technologies enable BrainHR to build scalable and secure software applications for clients. Java Server Pages (JSP) is a technology used for building dynamic web pages, which can be accessed through a web server. JSP allows for the creation of reusable components, easy debugging, and efficient handling of user requests. Java Servlets are server-side components that generate dynamic web content and allow interaction with client requests. They are used for handling HTTP requests, managing sessions, and managing server-side resources.

Java Database Connectivity (JDBC) is a standard API used for connecting to relational databases, which enables applications to perform database operations such as inserting, updating, deleting, and querying data. Enterprise Java Beans (EJB) is a component architecture for building scalable, distributed, and transactional enterprise applications. It allows for the separation of business logic from application logic, which facilitates the development of complex applications. Java Beans is a reusable software component that can be easily customized and manipulated to suit a wide range of applications. It is an important component of Java application development, allowing for modular design and rapid application development. Java Security is a key component of Java application development, ensuring the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and applications.

BrainHR has expertise in integrating and combining various tools and coding languages to execute a software project. JAX-RS, JAX-WS, SOAP, WSDL, Axis, Apache CXF are some of the Java-based web service frameworks used by BrainHR. Spring Web Flow, JSF, Log 4J, and JUnit are also employed for developing Java-based applications. RESTful and SOAP web services are implemented by BrainHR to provide easy access to software functionalities. BrainHR's expertise in integrating various tools and coding languages is crucial in executing software projects, as it allows for a more streamlined and efficient development process. JAX-RS, JAX-WS, SOAP, WSDL, Axis, and Apache CXF are all Java-based web service frameworks that BrainHR is well-versed in. These frameworks provide developers with a set of tools and libraries for building and consuming web services, allowing for easier and faster development of complex software systems.

In addition to Java-based web service frameworks, BrainHR also utilizes other technologies such as Spring Web Flow, JSF, Log 4J, and JUnit to develop Java-based applications. The Spring Web Flow framework provides an easy way to manage the flow of web applications, while JSF simplifies the development of user interfaces. Log 4J is used for logging and debugging, and Junit is utilized for unit testing to ensure that software applications meet client requirements. These tools allow for better organization and management of code, and help ensure the reliability and scalability of the final product. BrainHR employs RESTful and SOAP web services to provide easy access to software functionalities. These web services allow different software systems to communicate with each other, enabling the development of more complex and integrated software solutions. By using RESTful and SOAP web services, BrainHR can ensure that its clients have access to all the features and functionalities they need to run their businesses smoothly and efficiently.

At BrainHR, we use a Full Stack approach for building web applications using AngularJS and Spring MVC. We leverage AngularJS MVC to develop responsive and cross-browser compliant applications that provide a smooth user experience. We also implement various Java design patterns such as MVC, Session Facade, Data Access Object, Factory, Singleton, Data Transfer Object, and Front Controller to ensure optimal code structure and maintainability to build cross-browser compliant applications and implement various Java design patterns such as MVC, Session Facade, Data Access Object, Factory, Singleton, Data Transfer Object and Front Controller. We have experience in developing web applications using MVC design patterns like Spring MVC and have deployed Microservices architecture with Spring Boot based services & used Hibernate JPA for mapping java classes with Database and developed DAO objects and implemented data access layer using JPA-Hibernate to perform CRUD operations.

BrainHR provides services for the design and development of complex applications using Oracle SOA, UDDI, and WSDL. The company has experience in using various Integrated Development Environments (IDEs) such as Eclipse, NetBeans, IntelliJ, Spring Tool Suite, Visual Studio, and RAD. Spring, Hibernate, Spring MVC, SpringIOC, Spring Boot, and Spring Web Flow are some of the web service frameworks used by BrainHR to develop high-performance applications. We have experience in designing Web services, SOA based applications, writing Web services using WSDL, SOAP, RESTful with Jersey and UDDI in distributed web application development environment including writing ANT and Maven for builds and deployments to different environments and Logging tools like Log4J, SLF4J, and Splunk. These frameworks help to simplify the development process and reduce the time and effort required for development.

Spring provides features such as inversion of control, aspect-oriented programming, and various modules for developing web applications. The team at BrainHR has expertise in using various components of Spring, including Spring MVC, Spring IOC, and Spring Boot. Spring MVC is a web framework that provides a model-view-controller architecture for building web applications. Spring IOC is an inversion of control container that provides a mechanism for managing dependencies in a Java application. Spring Boot is a popular framework that provides a simplified way to create standalone, production-grade Spring-based applications. BrainHR leverages the power of these frameworks to develop scalable and efficient applications for its clients.

Another framework used by BrainHR is Hibernate, which is an object-relational mapping tool that provides a framework for mapping Java objects to relational databases. Hibernate simplifies the process of developing database-driven applications by reducing the amount of code needed to interact with the database. The team at BrainHR uses Hibernate to create efficient and scalable applications that can handle large amounts of data. Hibernate also provides features such as caching and lazy loading, which help to improve application performance. In addition to Spring and Hibernate, the team at BrainHR also has expertise in using other web service frameworks such as Struts, JSF, and Tapestry.

Application and web servers such as WebLogic Server 12c, WebSphere Application Server 8.5 known for its robustness, scalability, and security features, making it suitable for hosting mission-critical applications. Apache Tomcat is another popular web server used by BrainHR for deploying Java-based web applications. It is lightweight, easy to configure, and provides good performance for small to medium-sized applications. We use Apache Tomcat (8.5/8.0), Apache HTTP Server, IBM HTTP Server (8.5), and JBoss are used by BrainHR for deploying and hosting applications. These servers provide a reliable and secure environment for running software applications. BrainHR's team is also adept at deploying multiple high-performance MongoDB replica sets on AWS EC2 with robust reliability. We have experience in both framework and CloudFormation to automate AWS environment creation along with the ability to deploy on AWS, using build scripts and automate solutions using Shell and Python Scripts.

BrainHR has extensive experience in working with different databases such as Oracle (9i/10g/11g/12c), SQL Server (14.0), DB2, MySQL, and Postgre SQL. The company provides services for the design and implementation of NoSQL databases such as MongoDB, CouchDB, Cassandra, Dynamo DB, and Graph DB. In recent years, NoSQL databases have become increasingly popular due to their ability to handle unstructured and semi-structured data. BrainHR's experience in working with NoSQL databases such as MongoDB, CouchDB, Cassandra, Dynamo DB, and Graph DB allows them to provide clients with scalable and high-performance solutions for handling large volumes of data BrainHR uses MongoDB replica sets on AWS EC2 with robust reliability to deploy multiple high-performance databases. The company has experience in using both framework and CloudFormation to automate AWS environment creation along with the ability to deploy applications and servers on AWS services such as Elastic Beanstalk, CloudWatch etc

According to a recent report by Market Research Future, the global Java application server market is expected to grow at a CAGR of 8.7% during the forecast period 2017-2023. This highlights the growing trend towards the adoption of Java technologies in businesses across various industries. With BrainHR Java Services, you can be confident that you are partnering with a service provider that has the expertise and experience to help you achieve your goals and drive innovation in your organization.
